76561198042204542,Recommended,232910,24016713,"Posted: 2 July, 2016",all,Mumbles,"What is Trackmania² Stadium?Although I never actually got to play the original TrackMania or its successor ""Sunrise"" for any part, I regard Stadium as one of the best TrackMania games in the series. Essentially, this game is an arcade racer where you compete against the clock to see who can get the fastest time around the track. However there is a twist, if you're playing online, then be prepared to compete against 50 other people who are trying to do the same thing as you!It's a Ubisoft game... Will I need a UPlay account to play?Not really... You'll need a Maniaplanet account to play online, unless you're just interested in playing the game offline, then you won't need an account at all, but I highly recommend that you make an account.What's the customisation like in-game?Absolutely limitless! So you can create tracks in the track builder and then share them to the Steam Workshop, or share them to the ManiaExchange website which is the biggest collective of user-created tracks. As well as this, you can create skins for your cars, which includes colours and paint-jobs for the stadium car, as well as entirely different models for your car.Is racing against the clock the only thing you can do?Nope. There are a lot of user-implemented modes in this game. Some great examples are NASCAR, (you drive around ovals at break-neck speeds) RPG (which is essentially a very large track that can take from 5 minutes to an hour to complete) and the likes of other fantastic modes!How's the online community?In my opinion, the online community is the best part of the game. Back in the day, I used to play this game religiously and made loads of friends on the LOLMAPS server. (if you play on there a lot, what up it's Mumbles!) There's also an e-Gaming community behind this game, so if you think you're pretty good at this game, you can crank it up a notch and compete against the REAL good players.Do you recommend this game?Yes I do! If you manage to pick it up on the cheap, then even better! I also recommend trying out Canyon, Valley, Turbo and United Forever if you liked this game."
