76561197970585058,Recommended,232910,14792740,"Posted: 8 March, 2015",all,Varkster,"Played this for over 8k hours. Best game ever. And then Maniaplanet 4 was released. It's a little bit shinier, but a lot of the things that made the original game so fun (imo) have been removed. Bugs that many 'lol' tracks relied on have been 'fixed' and a lot of the old records are now unobtainable.I still reservedly recommend it; it's a good game. But with the update the appeal, for me at least, has been severly hammered.A very sad week; I doubt I'll be playing the new version anywhere near as much. :(Original review follows.---------------------------------Why so much time on what looks like a pretty basic, arcady, and completely unrealistic racing game?Well, after 3k+ hours, there are probably about 3k+ reasons. Let me try and pick a few.First off, this is very much skill-based. Even on the 'silly, luck' tracks (which I'll come to in a moment). Play online, and you'll find pro-level gamers showing almost unbelievable levels of skill and achieving the seemingly impossible. But it's not impossible - this is a very fair game. Any cheating is caught and eliminated pretty quickly. All the cars have the same spec, there is no car-to-car collision to mess up your times. It's (mostly) just you, and a track, and your level of skill that determine how well you do.Next, the variety. The track creator provided allows an almost limitless tracks, and the community has produced masses of content. This obviously varies enormously in both style and quality, but since you are generally only on any given track for 4-5 minutes, if you don't like one you just wait it out and see if the next is more your kind of thing. And probably, in those 4-5 minutes you'll try it anyway and still get sucked in to try and beat your own times at the very least.[continued in comments]"
