,Not Recommended,232910,11318266,"Posted: 19 July, 2014",all,BlazeHedgehog,"Trackmania 2: Stadium WAS the definitive way to play the game.Was.On May 9th, 2017 the game updated to a newer version of... well, everything. The login system changed, many of the graphics were changed, and other elements of the game were changed arbitrarily. I have spent nearly an hour just trying to play Trackmania 2 at all, but the game claimed my account didn't exist anymore and wouldn't let me reset my password.This is a problem, because even though Trackmania 2 downloaded a nearly 100mb patch, I had to log in to ManiaPlanet in order to download another 700mb of data. Otherwise, even if I tried to play in Offline mode without logging in, this new updated version of ManiaPlanet wouldn't have the necessary game data to even launch Trackmania 2 at all.After deciphering their broken password reset system and logging in, I found that the updated Trackmania 2 had erased all of my medals and ranks. This is because the new Trackmania 2 changed how vehicle physics work, so all of the old ranking data was invalid. This also breaks tons of custom tracks made over the last 3-5 years, which are the lifeblood of a game like this.Ubisoft and Nadeo have essentially decided to arbitrarily reset everything about Trackmania 2 without warning or any way to go back to the old game. For users just starting out from this point forward it's not going to be a big deal, but for a Trackmania veteran like me, an update like this is devastating.What a disaster."
