76561198040365578,Recommended,232910,11108597,"Posted: 6 July, 2014",all,Lulero,"To me racing games are ""good"" or ""bad"" depending on how many real players you'll face. To that respect this one is ""good"", but stick to the stadium version.It focuses on the player (you) skills to ride on the race with no collision between cars. To many this can feel like a gamebreaker but it remains unexpectly fun in all of the different available game mods. I'm talking about time attack, rounds or laps here. It really feels rewarding to finish 1st, or even get close to it. If the competion is that hard, not being relagated to the queue for being the worst player can be a rewarding achievement in itself.While everyting about it feels simple, easy to understand, from the controls to the rules they are also hard to master. You will get better and some rides will feel amazing. I'm not a fan of racing games but this one had me addicted. I don't play all the time but I always enjoy when I race on TM² Stadium. And as some famous anonymous guy said once: ""Time you enjoy wasting isn't wasted"".If you are trying to decide if that's a game for you, get it already (TM² Stadium) and give it a try. The production value is well worth the price."
